caption: Love this place, one of our favorite restaurants. This location has super friendly staff and the food was deelish as always. If you like meat or just need to load up on protein, this is your place! The house special and the garlic steak were my favorite this time. The sides are awesome - mashed potatoes to die for, crazy addictive cheesy bread and my favorite plantains. The salad bar is fantastic with all the choices around the garden you want. And if all the different steaks and cuts of meat, sausages and chicken are not enough,  the dessert list knocked my socks off. Try the chocolate cake... you'll thank me. I like their key lime pie too and the other choices are all just as tempting. We had a wonderful Valentines Day meal and we'll be back as long as they are in business. Highly recommend!!

This place would get 4 starts for coffee, food, and service - super friendly staff, delicious breakfast options, and good coffee. My only complaint is the wifi which is generally spotty at best and non functioning at worst. Come here and hang, but don't come to get work done.
Very nice little cafe. Loved that I was served my Darjeeling in a tea pot. How rare these days! A very nice place to relax. Thanks!
Excellent as usual!
Fabulous healthy food and drinks

It was so good that by the time I remembered to take a picture, I have already eaten it all. Ordered a bento box ( last item on bento menu- roll your own roll, cones with Norwegian salmon and brown rice  ) at 14. 95 per box. Plenty for quick lunch. Fresh, flavorful, good value for money.  I also ordered a miso soup. It an interesting version, tastes quite sour ( it has cilantro and lime in it). It is full of flavors and I know friends who would love it. For me, when it comes to miso soup, I prefer the basic original taste. So it is really love it or hate it. I am glad to try it, it is very good, just not my taste.
The tea was good. The ambiance not so much. I had the Moroccan mint tea and it was really good.

We had a really great experience at Teaism. The food was delicious, there was a lot of it, and the customer service was awesome. I personally recommend the Thai Chicken Curry. The sauce was exquisite, and the chicken was juicy. I also recommend the cabbage butts. The sauce used for this dish provides the perfect taste. And of course the tea, Kuding Tiasne, and ginger limeade very good.
Consistently great
Nice place to eat
Visit of necessity but great find, nonetheless! Nice variety of teas and perfectly prepared Boba.

Really good food for a quick healthy lunch. Had the grilled salmon which was super yummy. The space was also reasonably nice .although I wish people would put their plates and trays away after they got done. Do your bit people!
I only went for tea, so I can't speak for the food. The tea I had was delicious, but their selection is very limited
I have been there for lunch.  I find their offerings great and tasty.  I do recommend this place.
Great breakfast place. Super nice service and ambience inside and outside. The outside seating is great. I can highly recommend the scrambled eggs with jalapeños and salmon on the side.
Love the drinks
Allegedly has the best team according to my husband.
The bubble tea is not authentic but it is not bad
Interesting healthy lunch food, light and airy

Love the ambiance, the quick and healthy food, and the nice people.  The veggie curry just did not have enough flavor, and much of it was made up of a vegetable that was quite tough.  Either it was undercooked or should be cut into much smaller pieces.  But it was very pretty, and I will return here!
Great place to enjoy an Asian inspired meal and yummy deserts. We enjoyed a quiet spot by the window looking out at the fountain. Highly recommend it.
Amazing 👌 The food is to die for. I shelessly tried to recreate the salad I had there but it just wasn't the same! Will be going back for sure!
A D.C. gem! Incredible food and awesome, friendly staff.
Lovely service combined with an expansive selection of teas! Always order in to use the cute china
Pricey drink and meal spot in a cozy location of DC. I didn't particularly like the mango lassi, it was far too icey but the milk tea was fantastic.
(Translated by Google) Many homeless at night, the beauty of the park ends at that moment  (Original) Muchos homeless en la noche, la belleza del parque se acaba en ese momento
My favorite place for tea in DC

Really interesting idea with a wide variety of tea choices served in traditional tea pots! However, food was pretty good and healthy although as bit overpriced. Also, had a variety of Asian cuisine. We ordered Japanese, Thai, and Indian

Met here for a morning business meeting. My business associate is a tea fantatic (thus my choice of Teaism).....it was a winner. Tea choices garnered rave reviews. I had the Ginger Tea which was excellent. There are light breakfast offerings as well as a large selection of pastries. Enjoy!
Nice selection on the menu, but my vegetarian curry had zero spice.
First time here and I absolutely loved it! Teaism will definitely be a new favorite as they’re close to work, affordable, nice ambiance and great tea!
Good curry
A DC favorite for a delicious but casual lunch. One of the best places in the city to get loose leaf tea.
Their product is excellent but the service is consistently slow
Chicken curry was full of flavor and delicious.
Pretty good but also pretty pricey for what you get.
Always good...lots of tasty healthy food to choose from. Not cheap eats, but not outrageous either.  It would be nice if they had a larger selection of sweets to choose from.

Another great experience at Teaism. I usually visit the Dupont circle location, but deviated from the norm and tried this location instead. The oatmeal had a great consistentcy neither too runny nor too thick) Only downside was that it took surprisingly long for a simple order of oatmeal to be prepared.
This place is shite. Came in to do a spot of work after a lunch meeting and found that only one of their outlets was live.  So long as you don't need a charge, I suppose this spot would be passable.
Love the bubble tea

Quaint little spot for good cuisine and tea options. Have gone twice during the week for lunch carry out--once during rush hour (do NOT recommend- they were packed, but after tasting the food, I get it) and once at around 1:30, much lighter crowd and service was very prompt. I have only had the curry chicken and the Moroccan mint tea, but I stand by both of them. Seriously, the curried chicken is wonderful! Yes, $17 for a lunch entree and an iced tea is a little on the pricier side, but both items taste great, and I have not been able to finish the entree either time I've had it! If you are in the area, do yourself a favor and try this place out. You won't regret it...
Love going to this place! Great food!
Loved it, the food is amazing, perfect seasoning.
Delicious, healthy lunch, excellent menu selection
Good food and is a popular place.  Get there early.
I always love Teaism! Tons of options for everyone and always something new. This time I got a coconut miso broth in a cup, and it was phenomenal.
The salty oat cookies are the best. I also had the vegetable curry and it was amazing.  The chai is also delicious.  Not only does this place have amazing food and tea but it also a great interior.
Had some great food and Gluten Free cookies were the bomb
Love this place.  4.5 stars really.  Great chai and cookies.
One of my favorites in Washington D.C. Strongly recommended! 🍵🍪 ☯️
It's often crowded and surprisingly loud, and it's more of a restaurant than a dedicated tea shop. However, their tea selection is still better than most, and the food is actually pretty good.

Lovely place for a business meeting without the noise of a busy coffee shop. I just wish the teapot they brought me had hot water and not cold water in it. They replaced it with lukewarm water at best.
Nice place for a cup of tea, a quick bite or a fast lunch.
Arrugala and goat cheese salad is excellent.  Greens fresh and tasty. Also nice is the vegetarian curry.
The two best things on there menu are the Chai tea and the rice pudding.  These two things will brighten any gloomy day.
Great food and service.

I love teaism. Great food, tea. None of the locations have stellar service. I have food allergies and every time I inform the staff of this, I basically get an eye roll. Could do with some allergy training here. This location is very loud and small. It seems that it is busy but there were many available tables, it was extraordinarily loud due to the overwhelming amount of tile. This location is too small for the demand. The counter is very small and there is no where to put your purse down to get out your wallet to pay so get it out ahead of time. But if you love the food...
Good selection of food, but too crowded during lunch hours.
Food is fantastic and chai milkshake is amazing. But hard to get seating during the lunch rush and a little bit pricey.

The bubble tea was by far the best we have had since leaving Taiwan (where bubble tea was first made) but their menu options were a bit pricey. We got the udon noodles with vegetables and the ginger broth was strange. The soup was beautiful to look at but there was a rancid flavor to it like when garlic is over cooked. Also the basil just does not go well with the udon noodles. The atmosphere was lovely and we will definitely go back for the bubble tea.
I personally ordered their organic chicken curry, and it was the bomb. It can get busy during lunch, so maybe wait a bit if you are looking for that quiet tea shop atmosphere.
Always good chai and try the ginger scones
Wonderful, eclectic menu of food. Best teas, and cookies in the area. Great for a quick chat or a long cozy lunch.

Wonderful experience. Ordered the fried chicken bento box and changed all the sides (they allowed substitutions for different cold sides). Got the Asian slaw (which was just regular Cole slaw, very nice) the seaweed salad (classic style and fresh) and the beats ( my favorite of the three, tasted like a French side dish). The chicken was wonder, five pieces that were very hot and juicy with a very mild dipping sauce. Also ordered a green gazpacho, which was good, but not pureed fine enough for me. Definitely recommended.
Really like their black milk tea.
Teaism Lafayette Park
Great place for a stop when sightseeing in the White House neighborhood. Wide selection of teas and other refreshments.

Wonderful cafe for afternoon tea and pastries. Lunch is quite good but never enough food and on the expensive side.
Excellent chai! Pricey but tasty meals
Great food
I love Teaism but this isn't their best location.
Best food ever very healthy bit pricy really good customer service and the tea is amazing
Good food. Good prices
Great location with unique snacks, perfect to meet colleagues for a chat.
It has been a little bit since I've been here but they have great breakfast

I ordered food and tea online - and I was a little slow to pick it up, so the tea was no longer hot. Without asking, they automatically made me a fresh cup (even though it wasn't their fault that I was slow). The food was well prepared and the tea was excellent. Even though it was crowded (lunch time on a weekday), they were very efficient and moved the line quickly.
Nice selection of teas. Nibbles are available, and they're fine, if not worth a special trip. But if you want a place to go that isn't all about coffee or cocktails, it's perfectly pleasant.

The food is so good, the oatmeal cookies are so good, and the teas are so good. Breakfast and lunch here are both well worth it with tons of options for such a small place. If you're health and budget conscious for breakfast, try the muesli.
Casual work lunch place, good quick food.

I come here for bubble tea all the time, but I wish they had more flavors. The salmon bento is the great, but I don't know what the brown stuff is next to the broccoli. An olive tapenade or something?
Great. The only downside to this Teaism location is that it's not open on the weekend.

Teaism used to be sooooo delish then they changed their menu and the number of unusual and delish items reduced substantially. The other day we dropped into this one hoping it would be the same as the one in penn quarter that i usually go to and ordered their usually amazingly delicious chicken curry. What i received was a bowl of relatively thin chicken broth, chicken and rice with a skewer of barely warmed bitter vegetables - read way too al dente.  No more awesome think green curry with green beans that i crave regularly - i would not call this stuff curry at all and certainly won't be craving it. Everyone else were similarly unimpressed with their meals and we have now struck teaism from our lunch options. Cookies and udon were still great but bento boxes were plain in half the options and soaked in vinegar on the others.  Burgers crumbled and were tasteless. So bummed!
Come before noon to beat the lunch crowd. Delicious and healthy options and the best quality tea you will find in town. I love to get a bento box and bubble tea to go.
Ok
Good place for work-week lunch. Their Curry Chicken Salad is good.
This and the Dupont location are great for Saturday brunch. Try one of their bento boxes or omelettes. Favorite drink here is the Maroccan Mint.

This place has great food, and it is the food that keeps me as a frequent customer. The woman who works behind the register is not the nicest and doesn't add to my experience, but the food makes up for it. The cilantro eggs are a great way to start the morning; however, the curry lentil soup is what you really need to have. It doesn't have too much of a kick, but it is still great. If you're wondering the texture, it is not a pureed lentil, just split lentils with curry flavoring. Also, the salad dressing they use on their house salads is an orange based dressing that has to be tried.
Very good and inexpensive. Often very crowded though.
Decent food, good service during rush lunch time, in a rush I got a premade sandwich, which was decent, next time I will try something more complex.
Very nice moderately priced and exotic.
Nice place to relax & grab a bite
Great place to have lunch and to people watch(if you know what I mean)

When I take people here they either delight in their dish or find it kind of blah. The bento boxes are okay, but I thought the Seitan stir fry was fantastic. The Salty Oat Cookies are delicious. The location at Penn Quarter has a carp fountain/pond on the lower level that kids like to check out.
